#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Terminal review helper for branch changes.

review compares the current branch against a base ref, or compares two explicit
refs with --from and --to, shows changed files in a full-screen curses UI, and
stores per-file reviewed checkboxes under .git/review/<range>/state.json. The
default UI keeps a side-by-side diff at the top, a compact comment summary below
it, and the changed-file list at the bottom.

Local review comments are written directly into changed files with markers such
as "#review this is hard to read". Publishing scans those markers, creates
GitLab/GitHub MR or PR comments, remembers already published marker IDs, and
removes successfully published standalone marker lines from the working tree.
Inline markers are left untouched.

Remote discussions are auto-loaded when the UI starts and can be refreshed with
R. The comments popup groups published notes and visible pending review drafts
into threads, highlights replies, and allows replying to a selected remote
comment from inside the tool. Reply drafts are saved in the same review state
file and can be published later from the comments popup.

Useful keys in the UI:
- ? opens the in-app help popup.
- / starts regex file search.
- Space toggles the reviewed checkbox for the selected file.
- i toggles the ignored flag for the selected file.
- f cycles all/unchecked/checked/ignored filters.
- n/N jumps to the next or previous unreviewed file.
- c/e opens the selected file in the configured editor.
- d opens the selected diff in the pager.
- m opens the threaded comments popup; Up/Down or j/k select comments and draft
  rows, a saves a reply draft or edits the selected draft, P publishes the
  selected draft or all visible drafts, A applies the selected suggestion to the
  working tree, u undoes the last applied suggestion, x deletes the selected
  draft, r replies now, s toggles GitLab resolution, y copies the selected body,
  and g jumps to code.
- t opens the Jira ticket popup for JIRA_KEY or the issue key in the branch,
  shows ticket details and comments, and allows adding a Jira comment.
- o opens the current GitLab MR or GitHub PR in the browser.
- p publishes local #review markers, with output shown in a popup.

Editor selection for c/e and the edit subcommand follows normal shell defaults:
VISUAL is used first, then EDITOR, then nvim. Examples:
- VISUAL=zed review
- VISUAL="zed --wait" review
- VISUAL="code --wait" review
- EDITOR=vim review

For a lightweight picker instead of the full TUI, run "review --fast". It opens
fzf with a delta-powered preview above the file list and respects --base,
--from, and --to.

Use --ignore PATTERN to hide files from the review file list. The flag can be
passed multiple times and accepts exact paths, directory prefixes, or shell-style
globs:
- review --ignore 'tests/*'
- review status --ignore '*.md'
"""

